Not that we are sufficient of ourselves to think of anything as being from ourselves, but our sufficiency is from God. 
2 Corinthians 3:5. 

This Bible verse has been one of my favorites for some time now and maybe you’ve even noticed it in my bio.

This verse serves as a daily reminder to me that as a believer in Christ, my confidence and ability to serve God does not stem from my own strengths or accomplishments, but from the empowerment and guidance of the Holy Spirit. It emphasizes the importance of relying on God's grace and allowing His power to work through us.

More simply put, it stresses the need for humility, recognizing our limitations, and relying on God's sufficiency and provision in all aspects of our lives. 

Although this verse is a constant reminder for me, I still fall short and find myself trying to be self-reliant and self-sufficient. But, the good news is this, when we humble ourselves and acknowledge our inability, we can finally take the pressure off ourselves and rest fully in the capable and loving arms of the Lord who will bring us strength and freedom.

So my prayer for you and I is this, 
Lord, help us start living a life of God-sufficiency and God-reliance. Let us depend on You completely and trust that You will work through us for Your purpose. Lord, help us to develop a humility of heart that can only be found through total surrender to You. Praise God that in our weakness, You empower us to achieve all things. AMEN.

feeling good out here in Madrid. park semis tonight :) also placed 3rd in street semis yesterday. Let’s get it!

As most y’all probably saw, Madrid didn’t quite work out for me. Injured my ankle mid street finals and in turn had to pull out of the park finals the next day, which really bummed me out. Just cause i didn’t get the outcome i wanted doesn’t mean the work wasn’t worth it, though. I’m more motivated for the upcoming comps because of it and thankful to still have had the trip of a lifetime thanks to @luckyscooters. Let’s finish the rest of the comp season off right💪🏼
